# Talon — Always-On Context

**What it is:** Self-hosted personal AI gateway on a single Hostinger VPS.
**Runtime:** Python 3.12 / FastAPI / PostgreSQL+pgvector / React+Vite.
**Deployed as:** `talon.service` (systemd). Docker only for PostgreSQL + SearXNG.
**One operator. One server. No horizontal scaling.**

## Hardcoded Invariants

1. Secrets live in `config/secrets/` (chmod 700). Files chmod 600.
   Never in code, `.env`, or environment variables.

2. No synchronous I/O in async handlers. Use httpx, asyncpg, aiofiles.

3. All SQL via SQLAlchemy async ORM or parameterized queries. No interpolation.

4. LLM providers in priority order (configured in config/providers.yaml).
   Circuit breaker opens after 3 failures. All provider config in `config/providers.yaml`.

5. Skills implement `BaseSkill`. `execute()` returns `SkillResult` — never raises.

6. Tests mock the LLM gateway. Real provider calls use `@pytest.mark.llm_eval`.

7. SSE is the streaming transport. No WebSockets.

8. Frontend: TailwindCSS v4 + daisyUI v5. No raw CSS unless unavoidable.

9. Full type coverage: Python strict pyright, TypeScript strict mode, no `any`.

10. Every deploy runs `make test` first. A failing test suite does not ship.

## Key File Locations

```
backend/app/llm/gateway.py           LLM gateway + circuit breaker
backend/app/memory/engine.py         Memory engine (3-tier)
backend/app/skills/base.py           BaseSkill contract
backend/app/skills/registry.py       Dynamic skill loader
backend/app/core/config.py           Pydantic BaseSettings
backend/app/core/logging.py          structlog configuration
config/providers.yaml                LLM provider definitions
data/memories/                       Core memory Markdown sources
deploy/systemd/talon.service         systemd unit file
docker-compose.yml                   Auxiliary services only
```
